  "body": "\r\n# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\nI could not recreate this issue myself, but this was a problem for an user on discord:\r\n\r\nbeacon-chain is binding to 127.0.0.1:4000 by default now, but validator seems to be connecting to localhost:4000 by default. \r\nIn some cases it might happen that localhost is resolved to the IPv6 local address [::1] and a connection with the default parameters cannot be established, as beacon-chain is only listening on IPv4.\r\n\r\nA solution would be to either\r\n- bind beacon-chain to both interfaces or\r\n- have validator/slasher connect to 127.0.0.1 by default\r\n",
